This paper deals with the wiretap channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It specifically focuses on the Poisson wiretap channel with cost constraint, which is a sub-topic of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between reliability and security, which is a topic in communication complexity (cs.CC) and system security (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of concatenation and rate exchange, which are techniques commonly used in multimedia systems (cs.MM).
